meta.request.prompt: As Descartes said, I think, therefore
meta.response.choices.0.text: I am. And that means that my body, my mind, and my consciousness are all separate and distinct. This is the root of the dualism referred to as Cartesian dualism. It is my mind that is affecting my body by my thoughts and my emotions. I know that I am not the brain, the heart, or the liver and I am not the mind either. I am not a physical body. However, there is another part of me that is not physical and that is the “I” in the statement, “I think, therefore I am.” I am that so-called “I” that [TRUNCATED...]
